• 1. Project Scope        *
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
 The app draws a clock through the use of Quartz or OpenGL. The clock is updated 
 internally through timer. Once update the clock adjust to the new time that was 
 calculated.


•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
• 2. How to Build         *
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
 To build and run the application the file: Clock.xcodeproj must be opened on 
 Xcode then ran from it.


•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
• 3. How to Use           *
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
 The clock will automatically run once the app has been opened. When opening the app a 
 label will display the current time. Above it is the Clock face that redraws itself 
 whenever the time is updated. Currently the redrawing of the Clock has not been 
 implemented. 


•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
• 5. Bug/Limitations      *
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••
 There are no bugs in this application.
 Limitations: The redrawing of the Clock through Quartz has not been implemented. The only 
 part of the clock app that is working is the numerical display of the current time on the 
 label
 *At time of submission the project is incomplete*
 

